headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 34 points, setting a new franchise record with his 40th 30-point game this season, and the Boston Celtics rolled to a 120-95 win over the Indiana Pacers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum notches 40th 30-point game, Celtics beat Pacers 120-95

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Corey Kispert scored a career-high 26 points and sank six 3-pointers, Deni Avdija added 21 points and grabbed 11 rebounds, and the Washington Wizards pulled away for a 136-124 win over the San Antonio Spurs in a meeting of depleted teams Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kispert's 3s help Wizards pull away from Spurs 136-124

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 32 points, Chris Boucher had 19 points and 13 rebounds and the Toronto Raptors routed the struggling Detroit Pistons 118-97 on Friday night for their eighth win in nine home games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 32 as Raptors rout struggling Pistons 118-97

headlines.description: — Luke Kennard made a franchise-record 10 3-pointers to match his career high with 30 points, Desmond Bane added 25 points and the Memphis Grizzlies clinched a playoff spot after building a 31-point halftime lead and coasting to a 151-114 victory over...
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies clinch playoff berth with 151-114 rout of Rockets

headlines.description: — P.J. Washington Jr. scored 28 points and Gordon Hayward added 25 as the undermanned Charlotte Hornets built a 21-point lead and held on to beat the Dallas Mavericks 117-109 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Undermanned Hornets beat Doncic, Irving and Mavs 117-109

headlines.description: — Grayson Allen scored a season-high 25 points to lead the Milwaukee Bucks to a 144-116 victory over the Utah Jazz on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks overwhelm Jazz 144-116 for third straight victory

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole emerged as one of Golden State's most dependable performers during the championship run last season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors rally back from 11 down, beat Embiid, 76ers 120-112

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 33 points and the Chicago Bulls dominated the short-handed Portland Trail Blazers 124-96 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores 33, Bulls rout the Trail Blazers 124-96

headlines.description: — Kevin Huerter led all scorers with 29 points and the Sacramento Kings beat the Phoenix Suns 135-127 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Huerter scores 29 points, Kings beat Suns 135-127

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 37 points and 14 rebounds, Dennis Schröder added 13 of his 21 points in the fourth quarter and the Los Angeles Lakers got a vital victory for their playoff hopes, 116-111 over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis scores 37, Lakers hold off Thunder 116-111
